  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Coordinator",
  "description": "<ul><li>Coordinate daily site activities with the General Manager and Project Team to maintain project workflow</li><li>Participate in site surveys and assist with site inspections to verify project conditions and compliance</li><li>Prepare Bills of Quantities (BQ) and quotations to support project budgeting and client proposals</li><li>Develop project schedules, track progress updates, and create simple reports to communicate status</li><li>Communicate effectively with clients, contractors, suppliers, and internal team members to facilitate project coordination</li><li>Assist in Quality Assurance and Quality Control (QA/QC) activities on site to uphold project standards</li><li>Coordinate material deliveries and monitor availability of supplies to ensure uninterrupted site operations</li><li>Track usage of basic materials and tools on site to support inventory management</li><li>Prepare and maintain accurate project documents and records for reference and compliance</li><li>Perform other ad-hoc duties as assigned to support project needs APPLY<strong> NOW!</strong></li><li>Minimum ITE or NITEC qualification (or equivalent)</li><li>Candidates with no relevant experience are welcome to apply; training will be provided.</li><li>Good communications and administrative skills, able to meet deadlines, a team player, and a positive attitude.</li></ul>",
